ξ 3. iniurias : her ill—treatment by Nero.

Rubellius Plautus was son of Rubellius Blandus and Julia daughter of Drusus the son of Tiberius. He was recommended by Nero to go and live in Asia, in 60 Α. D. (Arm. xiv 22, 5), and was killed by Nero’s orders in 62 A. D., (Anu. xiv 59, 3).
